If you only want to read the values of `battles` and `email`, first of all, there is no need to attach a persistent listener. You can only call [get()][1] and read the values. Besides that, since there is a single child in your database, there is no need to iterate over the DataSnapshot object. So in code, it will be as simple as:

	DatabaseReference db = FirebaseDatabase.getInstance().getReference();
    db.child(&quot;mail@gmailcom&quot;).get().addOnCompleteListener(new OnCompleteListener&lt;DataSnapshot&gt;() {
		@Override
		public void onComplete(@NonNull Task&lt;DataSnapshot&gt; task) {
			if (task.isSuccessful()) {
				DataSnapshot snapshot = task.getResult();
                long battles = snapshot.child(&quot;battles&quot;).getValue(Long.class);
                String email = snapshot.child(&quot;email&quot;).getValue(String.class);
				Log.d(&quot;TAG&quot;, battles + &quot;/&quot; + email);
			} else {
				Log.d(&quot;TAG&quot;, task.getException().getMessage()); //Never ignore potential errors!
			}
		}
	});

The result in the logcat will be:

    5000/mail@gmailcom

  [1]: https://firebase.google.com/docs/reference/android/com/google/firebase/firestore/Query#get()

